"<h1>頁面源代碼</h1>\n\n<div class=\"page-source\">\n\t[[include <a href=\"http://scp-zh-tr.wikidot.com/theme:black-highlighter-theme\">:scp-zh-tr:theme:black-highlighter-theme</a>]]<br />\n[[include <a href=\"http://scp-zh-tr.wikidot.com/theme:dustjacket\">:scp-zh-tr:theme:dustjacket</a>]]<br />\n[[module css]]<br />\n[id*=&quot;toc&quot;] {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;text-align: center;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n.yui-navset .yui-nav li a em, .yui-navset-top .yui-nav li a em, .yui-navset-bottom .yui-nav li a em {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-family: var(--header-font);<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-size: 120%;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n.yui-content {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 1em 2em !important;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\ndiv.inner {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 1em !important;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n.yui-content ul {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 0 1em;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;margin: 0 auto;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;width: 80%;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n.yui-content ol {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 0 1em;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;margin: 0 auto;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;width: 80%;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;list-style-position: inside;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;list-style: none;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;counter-reset: li;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n#main-content .yui-content li {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;padding: 0 0 1em 0;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;counter-increment: li;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\n#main-content .yui-content ol li::before {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;content: counter(li) &quot;.&quot;;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;color: rgb(var(--swatch-menubg-dark-color));<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-family: var(--header-font);<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-size: 175%;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;display: inline-block;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;width: 1em;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;margin-left: -1em;<br />\n}<br />\n<br />\ndiv.inner.about {<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;font-size: 120%;<br />\n}<br />\n[[/module]]<br />\n[[include <a href=\"/info:start\">info:start</a>]]<br />\n原文:[http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/orientation Orientation]<br />\n譯者:[[*user 42anonymous]]<br />\n-----<br />\n來自ZH分館的補充，由於網站性質與流浪者圖書館本館存在著差異，不是獨立網站與網站規則相異等等，為了避免用戶混亂，所以部分譯文有經過一定程度的改寫。<br />\n[[include <a href=\"/info:end\">info:end</a>]]<br />\n[[tabview]]<br />\n[[tab 介紹]]<br />\n+ 歡迎來到流浪者的圖書館。<br />\n<br />\n[[div_ class=&quot;fancyborder&quot;]]<br />\nThe Wanderer's Library is a collaborative fiction exercise. It's a collection of stories that explore strange and fantastic corners of the world, hidden from ordinary eyes. Some of the stories take place in the distant past, taking the form of legends and fables. Others are from the modern day, hiding in the shadows just out of sight. The basic premise is that there are strange things that are not quite of our world. Some are dangerous, some are merely fascinating. They are all in some respect extraordinary.<br />\n<br />\nA big game hunter searches for hunting in other worlds.<br />\n<br />\nA creature lives in alleyways and junkyards, collecting bits of trash to disguise itself.<br />\n<br />\nA red thing of many parts promises everything you have ever wanted.<br />\n<br />\nStories here should try to evoke a Sense of Wonder, a sense that there is a larger world beyond the one we know. In the world of the Library, these wonders are hidden, but never truly far away. But never forget that this is a wilder world than our own, and it's never entirely safe, either. Tread with care.<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n<br />\n++ Give the rules a once-over. After that, choose your own adventure:<br />\n<br />\n[[size 120%]]<br />\n* To read the works collected in the Library, go to [[[wanderers:The Library|圖書館]]]. (This is the option most of you will want to pick.)<br />\n* To learn more about the groups and entities that populate the Library and many other worlds besides, go to [http://scp-zh-tr.com/wanderers:thearchivistslog Archivist's Log].<br />\n* Before you **post** anything you've already written, read this: http://scp-zh-tr.wikidot.com/wanderers:forum/t-542611/license<br />\n[[/tab]]<br />\n[[tab 規則]]<br />\n+++ These are our rules-in-progress. Breaking these rules can result in being warned by staff, having restrictions placed on you, temporarily revoking your membership, or being banned.<br />\n<br />\n------<br />\n<br />\n++ **一般**<br />\n[[size 120%]]<br />\n* Basic internet etiquette applies here. Being harsh is fine, but don't be an asshole, and definitely don't go trolling. No harassment of other users. (Note: Writing badly will //not// get you banned.)<br />\n* When you post on the site: Please post completed works! (Or, you know, completed chapters or sections. That sort of thing.) Drafts go in [http://wanderers-sandbox.wikidot.com/ the Wanderer's Sandbox].<br />\n* If you disagree with any staff decision, feel free to contact another staff member, but don't just keep trying til you get a different answer. If you feel a user is breaking a rule, please contact staff.<br />\n* Please refrain from contentless or pointlessly nonsensical posts (i.e. &quot;shitposting&quot;). This applies to critique as well. Repeated infractions will lead to escalating consequences.<br />\n[[/size]]<br />\n++ 評論與投票<br />\n[[size 120%]]<br />\n* You may comment however you like on an entry, as long as you're not trolling, making a personal attack, or posting just to post (see &quot;shitposting,&quot; above).<br />\n* You may vote however you like on any entry, as long as you're voting on the //entry//. Not on whether you like or dislike the author, or for some other reason not related to the entry's quality.<br />\n[[/size]]<br />\n++ 編輯<br />\n[[size 120%]]<br />\n* You can edit others' articles for reasons for format, grammar/spelling, or other minor edits. Don't make edits for content without the author's permission. Not even if the content is //terrible//. This goes for staff too.<br />\n[[/size]]<br />\n++ 刪除<br />\n[[size 120%]]<br />\n* When a page rating hits -5, the page may be deleted at staff discretion. <br />\n* Users may delete their own work at any time. You can do this by going to the bottom of the page, clicking &quot;Options,&quot; and clicking on &quot;Delete.&quot;<br />\n* Click &quot;delete completely&quot; and confirm your decision. //Do not click &quot;Just rename.&quot;//<br />\n[[/size]]<br />\n+++ 作者頁面<br />\n[[=]]<br />\nWhen you have created two or more pages, you can add an author page linking all your work together. Author pages are indexed [[[http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/members-pages| here]]].<br />\n[[/=]]<br />\n++ 其他<br />\n<br />\n* We reserve the right to add, remove, or modify rules at our discretion. Considering this is a rules-in-progress page, this certainly //will// happen.<br />\n[[/size]]<br />\n<br />\n[[/tab]]<br />\n[[tab 認識員工]]<br />\n[[=]]<br />\n+ **Admins**<br />\n<br />\n+++ **[*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/the-strange-fiction-of-j-ryan-beattie Dr. Everett Mann]** <br />\nThe mysterious stranger who founded this site. Master admin. Not often paying attention to chat, but can be reached through PMs. Very cool, if you can get ahold of him.<br />\n<br />\n+++ **[*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/rumetzen Rumetzen]** <br />\nManaged to trick people into thinking he's a good writer through the tactical application of pathos. On a good portion of the time, and always up for looking at drafts. Better at helping with prose, dialogue, and the other technical aspects of writing than ideas or story. Also goes by &quot;Rheumatism&quot;, which should tell you everything you need to know, really.<br />\n<br />\n+++ **[*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/on-loan-from-r-j-clinton Roget]** <br />\n--The longest serving non-administrative staff member-- haha psych, as well as your mother's cousin's best friend's former roommate, Roget is --supposedly-- a pretty nice guy and usually willing to help you out. He is best at ideas and overall content rather than mechanical issues. Very active on chat so if you have a draft, be sure to pitch it to him. Also an admin on the SCP wiki, so if you have an SCP draft he can review those as well. We don't quite know how he does it, but he always wins at hopscotch.<br />\n<br />\n++ **Moderation**<br />\n<br />\n++++ **Rounderhouse** <br />\nLocal yurt who successfully managed to look more responsible than he really is. Is usually willing to lend a hand to any users in need - except with critique. Good prose is his archenemy. Pretty active on chat.<br />\n<br />\n++++ **Woedenaz** <br />\nMostly here to make things look pretty. Roget called; Woedenaz answered. Can write CSS in hours. Takes months/years to write any actual stories. Quite active in chat if needed.<br />\n<br />\n------<br />\n<br />\n**Staff MIA:** Pair of Ducks, [*http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel tunedtoadeadchannel], [*http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose thedeadlymoose], [*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/the-archivist-s-desk TroyL], [*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/septimus-the-enchanter Vivax], [*http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/Pixeltasim Pixeltasim], [*http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/ozan-soner-ayhan Gaffney], [*http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jack-manganese Jack Manganese]<br />\n[[/=]]<br />\n[[/tab]]<br />\n[[tab 圖書館宇宙]]<br />\n@@ @@<br />\n[[div_ class=&quot;fancyborder&quot;]]<br />\n[[size 130%]]流浪者圖書館是個充滿不同故事的地方，這些故事彷彿讓人來到一個新天地一般，從壯麗的奇聞軼事到短篇的無韻詩，甚至是影像和視覺藝術。將所有不同的故事聯繫在一起的便是圖書館及其世界（們）。[[/size]]<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n[[div class=&quot;inner about&quot;]]<br />\n<br />\n[[=]]<br />\n+ 那麼，//圖書館是什麼//？<br />\n[[/=]]<br />\n<br />\n**圖書館** 存在於正常空間之外，包含了所有，甚至許多從未被撰寫的書。不論在哪個世界，各地都有通往圖書館的大門。如果你爬到書架的頂部向遠處眺望，只會有無窮無盡的書架映入眼簾；這座建築物如同其他圖書館一般，只不過比其他人造建築還要大上許多。<br />\n<br />\n就人們所知，圖書館存在是為了收藏與提供書籍和信息，因此所有人都能前來查閱書籍或其他形式的館藏。圖書館的許多創作對前來到此地造訪的人來說十分神秘。在眾多館藏中，有些創作被稱為Archives，只有少數人得以借閱；其它館藏則能經由圖書館館員之手借出。<br />\n<br />\n-----<br />\n圖書館有一些簡單的規則：準時歸還借閱之書籍，不得損壞書籍，不得竊取書籍，不得破壞圖書館財產，不得傷害圖書館內的人。那些不能或不願意遵守規則的人們，則會加入圖書館館員的行列[[footnote]] 不遵守規則者將成為圖書館館員的一分子，以勞動補償其違規行為 [[/footnote]]。<br />\n<br />\n圖書館館員是圖書館的管理者，負責監督與日常維護。前來的讀者們可能會遇到三種類型中的其中一種。<br />\n<br />\n**//Archivist//**在大廳的櫃台為人們服務。它們沒有眼睛，但它們能本能地在圖書館中找到任何館藏，它們也負責發放圖書借閱證、辦理書籍借閱以及追蹤每本書目前的所在之處。如果你往櫃台裡瞧，你會發現它們並沒有腿，而是直接連接在固定於大理石地板的椅子上。<br />\n<br />\n**//Page//**負責整理書架上的書籍。它們擁有六到十隻手臂、弓形的雙腿和矮胖的身體，使得它們非常擅長於攀爬，能夠在不需要梯子的情況下到達最上層的書架，因此它們極少處於地面。<br />\n<br />\n**//Docent//**負責在圖書館中引導讀者，向人們指示可以在哪裡找到他們需要的書籍，同時它們也時時刻刻地注意著館內是否有任何違規行為。它們無聲無息，事實上，它們甚至沒有嘴巴。一條鍊子從本該是它們左手的部分長出，鍊子的末端則連接著一個永不熄滅的黃銅燈籠。<br />\n<br />\nDocent身為圖書館的第一道防線，特別負責對抗敵對實體。有人說他們甚至能在任何存在通過**Way**之前就感覺到對方的敵意，儘管這種說法目前仍有爭議。<br />\n------<br />\n**//Way//**是各個世界與不同現實之間的聯繫，而圖書館是所有世界的中繼站，幾乎每個世界都存在至少一道Way與之相連。<br />\n<br />\n它們以不同的形式出現，從一扇門到一座拱門，甚至可以是一面鏡子。如果想要進門，必須得先「敲門」，也就是執行特定的動作或滿足某些特定的條件，可能是以口哨吹出特定的音調，可能是帶上一株有七片葉子的幸運草，也可能是把一捲VHS錄影帶版本的《龍爭虎鬥》洗掉。只要「敲門」，穿過那扇門，你就能發現自己到達一個全新的世界。<br />\n<br />\n並非所有的Way都能通往圖書館，有些通往其他世界，有些則通往同一個世界的其他地方。至今即使是才智最為出眾的人們，包括蛇之手中的那些，也無法了解它們是如何運作的。目前尚未有人解明Way的運作機制，前提是如果它們的運作方式存在機制的話。<br />\n-----<br />\n**//蛇之手//**是一群相信超自然現象不應被壓抑或保密的人，每個成員的個人意識形態以及處事方法都十分地不同。比起稱作一個組織，他們更像是一種組織結構鬆散的社會運動。蛇之手有各式各樣的成員，從想向他人展示所學的普通人，到那些天賦異稟的人們，甚至是渴望被人類社會接受的非人類實體。<br />\n<br />\n雖然對於該組織究竟存在多久仍有爭議，多數人一致認為蛇之手至少從19世紀末以來便以某種形式存在。由於不明原因，蛇之手曾有一段時間無法造訪圖書館，直到1967年，圖書館才被蛇之手「重新發現」。<br />\n<br />\n儘管蛇之手與圖書館密切相關，但兩者之間並沒有直接關係。圖書館是蛇之手的營運基地和會館，但蛇之手在任何方面都沒有對其有所有權。<br />\n<br />\n蛇之手並不是中央集權的組織，其中有數十個不同的派別和團體，每個派別雖都打著蛇之手的名義，但皆以自身的意志行事，因蛇之手成員只須遵守「願意將自己視為蛇之手中的一員」這唯一一條規則，導致他們缺乏組織性。最重要的是，蛇之手是那些希望更了解世界的人們的保護傘，它既不要求其成員做出承諾，也沒有做出任何承諾。<br />\n<br />\n話雖這麼說，人們更有可能被蛇之手中一些勇於行動、知識淵博或者較有魅力的人吸引。其中一個這樣的人物便是L.S.，他是蛇之手中其中一個激進派的領導人。L.S.非但沒有避免與基金會和全球超自然聯盟等組織交手，甚至與之爭鋒相對。儘管 [http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-268&nbsp;&nbsp;從未露臉]，但L.S.已經為該派系贏得了響亮的名聲。<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n[[/tab]]<br />\n[[tab 寫作指南]]<br />\n&nbsp;如果你從基金會的頁面來到這，你也許會知道如何發布一篇文章，但如果你從未去過，那麼這篇文章將會為你詳細地說明。<br />\n<br />\n[[div_ class=&quot;inner&quot;]]<br />\n+++ 提出點子<br />\n<br />\n流浪者圖書館是一個非常自由的寫作形式。這裡的故事包羅萬象，而創造它們也十分有趣。不幸的是，這種高度開放性也會讓人不知道該從哪裡開始下手。這裡有一些能夠幫到你的提示：<br />\n<br />\n[[ol]]<br />\n[[li]]在論壇和聊天室中與人討論。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]也許你可以在[[[http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/the-things-you-find| 那些你找到的東西]]] 中找尋靈感，又或者，如果你想尋找更多多媒體或長篇形式的作品，可以試試在[http://wanderers-library.wikidot.com/forum/t-519509/what-are-some-good-inspirations-for-library-material 靈感討論區]中找找。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]記住，你可以使用任何主題創作，而從生活中找尋靈感是最簡單的方法。你能以任何有關日常生活中讓你覺得奇怪或有趣的事情為題材撰寫故事，若你有個「如果……會怎麼樣？」的構想，就大膽地下筆吧。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]不要害怕做出新的嘗試，如果你想讓你的作品包含[[[Hidden Corners of Places |照片]]]、[[[I. Orion- |繪畫]]]、[[[The Back Pages |廣告]]]、[[[And We Slipped Away |或是]]] [[[sedna v arnaaluk the qaqulluk&nbsp;&nbsp;|詭異的]]] [[[A Series of Irksome Rectangles&nbsp;&nbsp;|格式]]]的話 ，就放手去做吧。如果你需要幫忙，可以到聊天室、論壇或是私訊其他人討論，我們很歡迎各位在網站上加入非文字的元素。[[/li]]<br />\n[[/ol]]<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n@@ @@<br />\n[[div_ class=&quot;inner&quot;]]<br />\n+++ 發帖<br />\n[[ol]]<br />\n[[li]]首先，你必須寫一個故事。「一個故事」可以以任何形式呈現，它可以是一組帶有幾行文字的圖片（我們有一些這樣的作品）、藝術品、詩歌、散文 – 沒有任何限制。建議你先在沙盒或word文檔中撰寫，而非直接在wiki上發布文章。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]在聊天室和論壇中讓你的其他同伴們評論你的作品。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]如果你覺得是時候發帖了，點選側欄中的「站點資訊查詢」，接著開啟「創建新頁面」的頁面，在頁面最下方能夠找到圖書館的板塊，跟隨提示創建即可。你能在那裡發佈你的故事。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]大功告成！現在你可以離開創作的頁面，系統將會把它添加到當前的公告中，好讓聊天室中的人們看到你的創作。如果你有作者頁面，別忘了在創建新故事時一併更新。[[/li]]<br />\n[[/ol]]<br />\n記得放上評分模塊（將以下的代碼放在創作頁面的最上方）<br />\n&gt; @@[[&gt;]]@@<br />\n&gt; @@[[module Rate]]@@<br />\n&gt; @@[[/&gt;]]@@<br />\n<br />\n之後，你可以[[[/contribute|在論壇中發佈你的創作]]]並和其他人討論。<br />\n<br />\n就快完成了！只剩下一步......<br />\n<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n@@ @@<br />\n[[div_ class=&quot;inner&quot;]]<br />\n+++ 標記<br />\n[[ol]]<br />\n[[li]]讓工作人員為你的文章添加標籤，[[[/tag-guide#toc6|標籤列表]]]可以在這裡找到。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]除非你知道自己在做甚麼，否則請讓工作人員進行標記。[[/li]]<br />\n[[li]]大功告成！[[/li]]<br />\n[[/ol]]<br />\n[[/div]]<br />\n[[/tab]]<br />\n[[/tabview]]\n</div>\n"